faa4ede2c9c5d62f1e00	youtube	https://youtu.be/DpSEX3h6RM4	skills/customer-acquisition/SKILL.md	customer-acquisition	Proven strategies to acquire your first 5-10 customers for startups and side projects. Use when launching a product, finding early adopters, or validating business ideas.	\n# Customer Acquisition - First 5 Customers\n\nProven strategies to get your first paying customers from scratch.\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Launching a new product/service\n- Need first paying customers\n- Validating business idea\n- Building early traction\n- Pre-seed/startup phase\n- Side project monetization\n\n## The First 5 Customers Framework\n\n### Customer #1: Friends & Family (Warm Network)\n\n**Strategy:** Personal outreach to people who already trust you\n\n**Action Steps:**\n1. List 20 people you know (friends, family, colleagues)\n2. Identify 5-7 who fit your target market\n3. Send personal message (not broadcast!)\n4. Offer founding member discount (50% off)\n5. Get on a call to understand their needs\n\n**Script:**\n```\n"Hey [Name]! I'm working on [product] that helps [target audience] \nsolve [problem]. I know you [relevant context about them]. \n\nWould you be open to a 15-min call this week to see if this \ncould help you? Happy to give you founding member pricing if \nit's a fit!"\n```\n\n**Expected Close Rate:** 10-20% (1-2 customers)\n\n---\n\n### Customer #2: Direct Outreach (Cold but Targeted)\n\n**Strategy:** Identify and reach out to ideal customers directly\n\n**Action Steps:**\n1. Define your ideal customer profile (ICP)\n2. Find 50 prospects (LinkedIn, Twitter, indie hacker communities)\n3. Craft personalized outreach message\n4. Send 10-15 messages/day\n5. Follow up 2-3 times (most say yes on 3rd follow-up!)\n\n**Where to Find Prospects:**\n- LinkedIn (search by job title + industry)\n- Twitter (search for problem keywords)\n- Indie Hackers community\n- Reddit (relevant subreddits)\n- Facebook Groups\n- Slack/Discord communities\n\n**Outreach Template:**\n```\n"Hi [Name],\n\nI saw your [post/profile] about [specific problem they mentioned].\n\nI built [product] that specifically solves this for [their role]. \nWe've helped [similar person/company] achieve [result].\n\nWould you be open to a quick 15-min demo this week? No pressure \nat all - even if it's not a fit, I'd love your feedback.\n\nBest,\n[Your name]"\n```\n\n**Expected Close Rate:** 2-5% (1-2 customers from 50 outreaches)\n\n---\n\n### Customer #3: Content Marketing (Inbound)\n\n**Strategy:** Create valuable content that attracts customers\n\n**Action Steps:**\n1. Identify where your customers hang out online\n2. Create 3-5 pieces of helpful content\n3. Share in relevant communities (no spam!)\n4. Include clear CTA (call-to-action)\n5. Respond to every comment/message\n\n**Content Ideas:**\n- "How I solved [problem]" tutorial\n- Case study: "[Customer] achieved [result]"\n- "5 mistakes people make with [problem]"\n- Free tool/resource related to your product\n- Behind-the-scenes of building your product\n\n**Distribution Channels:**\n- Twitter/X threads\n- LinkedIn posts\n- Reddit (relevant subreddits)\n- Indie Hackers\n- Hacker News\n- Product Hunt (launch day)\n- YouTube Shorts/TikToks\n\n**Expected Timeline:** 2-4 weeks to see results  \n**Expected Close Rate:** 1-3 customers per month\n\n---\n\n### Customer #4: Partnerships & Integrations\n\n**Strategy:** Leverage existing audiences and platforms\n\n**Action Steps:**\n1. Identify complementary products/services\n2. Reach out to founders (not big companies!)\n3. Propose win-win partnership\n4. Co-create content or bundle offerings\n5. Cross-promote to each other's audiences\n\n**Partnership Ideas:**\n- Guest podcast appearances\n- Co-hosted webinars\n- Bundle deals (your product + theirs)\n- Integration partnerships\n- Affiliate/referral programs\n- Joint content (blog posts, videos)\n\n**Outreach Template:**\n```\n"Hi [Founder Name],\n\nLove what you're building with [their product]! \n\nI run [your product] - we help [shared target audience] with \n[complementary problem]. Our audiences would overlap perfectly.\n\nWould you be open to exploring a partnership? Ideas:\n- Co-hosted webinar\n- Bundle deal for our customers\n- Guest swap (podcast/blog)\n\nLet me know if you'd like to chat!\n\nBest,\n[Your name]"\n```\n\n**Expected Close Rate:** 10-20% of partnerships  \n**Expected Customers:** 1-2 per successful partnership\n\n---\n\n### Customer #5: Paid Ads (Once You Have Traction)\n\n**Strategy:** Use paid advertising once you have proof\n\n**⚠️ WARNING:** Only do this AFTER you have:\n- ✅ 3-4 organic customers\n- ✅ Clear value proposition\n- ✅ Landing page that converts\n- ✅ Budget to test ($100-500 minimum)\n\n**Best Platforms for B2B:**\n- LinkedIn Ads (expensive but targeted)\n- Twitter Ads (good for tech/SaaS)\n- Google Ads (high intent)\n- Reddit Ads (niche audiences)\n\n**Best Platforms for B2C:**\n- Facebook/Instagram Ads\n- TikTok Ads\n- YouTube Ads\n- Google Ads\n\n**Starting Budget:** $10-20/day  \n**Test Period:** 7-14 days minimum  \n**Goal:** CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost) < LTV (Lifetime Value) / 3\n\n---\n\n## Quick Wins (First 48 Hours)\n\n### 1. Post on Social Media\n\n**Twitter/X Template:**\n```\n🚀 Just launched [product]!\n\nHelps [target audience] solve [problem] without [common pain point].\n\nLooking for 5 beta users to try it free + give feedback.\n\nDM me if interested! 👋\n\n#buildinpublic #startup #SaaS\n```\n\n**LinkedIn Template:**\n```\nExcited to share what I've been building...\n\n[Product] helps [target audience] achieve [result] in [timeframe].\n\nAfter [X months] of development, we're finally ready for beta users.\n\nLooking for 5 companies to try it free in exchange for honest feedback.\n\nKnow anyone who might be interested? Tag them below! 👇\n```\n\n### 2. Join Communities & Help\n\n**Strategy:** Be helpful first, sell second\n\n**Action Plan:**\n1. Join 3-5 relevant communities\n2. Spend 30 min/day answering questions\n3. Only mention your product when genuinely relevant\n4. Build reputation as helpful expert\n5. Customers will come to you\n\n**Communities to Join:**\n- Indie Hackers\n- r/SaaS (Reddit)\n- r/entrepreneur (Reddit)\n- Twitter #buildinpublic community\n- LinkedIn groups (your industry)\n- Slack/Discord communities\n\n### 3. Offer Free Trial + Bonus\n\n**Incentive Structure:**\n```\n🎁 Founding Member Offer:\n\n✅ 50% off for life\n✅ Priority support (direct access to me)\n✅ Input on product roadmap\n✅ Free onboarding call\n✅ 30-day money-back guarantee\n\nLimited to first 10 customers only!\n```\n\n**Urgency:** "Only X spots left!"  \n**Risk Reversal:** "30-day money-back guarantee"\n\n---\n\n## Tracking & Metrics\n\n### Daily Activities\n\n| Activity | Target | Actual |\n|----------|--------|--------|\n| Personal outreaches | 5 | ___ |\n| Cold outreaches | 10-15 | ___ |\n| Content pieces | 1 | ___ |\n| Community interactions | 5 | ___ |\n| Follow-ups | 10 | ___ |\n\n### Weekly Metrics\n\n| Metric | Week 1 | Week 2 | Week 3 | Week 4 |\n|--------|--------|--------|--------|--------|\n| Total outreaches | | | | |\n| Responses | | | | |\n| Calls booked | | | | |\n| Customers acquired | | | | |\n| Revenue | | | | |\n\n### Key Metrics to Track\n\n- **Outreach → Response Rate:** Target 20-30%\n- **Response → Call Rate:** Target 30-50%\n- **Call → Close Rate:** Target 20-40%\n- **Overall Conversion:** Target 2-5% (outreach to customer)\n- **CAC:** Target < $100 for first 10 customers\n- **Time to First Customer:** Target < 2 weeks\n\n---\n\n## Common Mistakes to Avoid\n\n### ❌ Mistake #1: Building in Silence\n\n**Wrong:** Spend 6 months building, then launch to crickets\n\n**Right:** Get customers BEFORE you finish building\n- Share progress publicly\n- Get beta testers early\n- Iterate based on feedback\n\n### ❌ Mistake #2: Waiting for Perfect Product\n\n**Wrong:** "I'll start selling when [feature X] is done"\n\n**Right:** Sell the vision, deliver manually if needed\n- First customers buy the outcome, not features\n- Manual work is fine initially\n- Automate after you have paying customers\n\n### ❌ Mistake #3: Generic Outreach\n\n**Wrong:** "Hi, check out my product!"\n\n**Right:** Personalized, specific, helpful\n- Mention something specific about them\n- Show you understand their problem\n- Offer value before asking for sale\n\n### ❌ Mistake #4: Giving Up Too Soon\n\n**Wrong:** Send 10 messages, get no replies, quit\n\n**Right:** Persist for at least 30 days\n- Most customers come from follow-ups\n- Average sale happens on 5th-7th touch\n- Consistency beats intensity\n\n### ❌ Mistake #5: No Clear CTA\n\n**Wrong:** "Let me know what you think!"\n\n**Right:** Clear, specific next step\n- "Are you free Tuesday at 2pm for a 15-min demo?"\n- "Can I send you a free trial account?"\n- "Would you like to hop on a quick call?"\n\n---\n\n## Scripts & Templates\n\n### Cold Email Template (High Converting)\n\n```\nSubject: Quick question about [specific problem]\n\nHi [Name],\n\nI noticed [specific observation about their company/situation].\n\nI help [similar companies/people] solve [problem] and achieve \n[result] in [timeframe].\n\nRecent example: [Customer] went from [before] to [after] in \n[timeframe].\n\nWould you be open to a 15-minute call this week to see if we \ncould do the same for you?\n\nNo pressure at all - even if it's not a fit, I'd love your \nthoughts on [relevant topic].\n\nBest,\n[Your name]\n\nP.S. [Optional: Add social proof or interesting stat]\n```\n\n### Follow-Up Sequence (5 Touches)\n\n**Day 1:** Initial outreach (see template above)\n\n**Day 3:** \n```\n"Hey [Name], just bumping this up in case it got buried. \nStill happy to hop on a quick call if you're interested!"\n```\n\n**Day 7:**\n```\n"Hi [Name], I know you're busy so I won't keep following up. \n\nIf [problem] is still a priority for you, feel free to reach \nout anytime. Here's my calendar: [link]\n\nEither way, wish you the best with [their company/project]!"\n```\n\n**Day 14:** (Value add)\n```\n"Hey [Name], saw this [article/resource] and thought of you: \n[link]\n\nMight be helpful for [specific challenge they mentioned].\n\nStill happy to chat about [your product] if you're interested, \nbut no pressure at all!"\n```\n\n**Day 30:** (Break-up)\n```\n"Hi [Name], I assume [problem] isn't a priority right now or \nyou've found a solution.\n\nI'll stop reaching out, but feel free to connect if things \nchange. Best of luck with everything!"\n```\n\n**Stats:** 80% of responses come from touches 3-5!\n\n---\n\n## Success Stories\n\n### Example 1: B2B SaaS (First 5 Customers)\n\n**Product:** Email automation tool for recruiters\n\n**Timeline:** 3 weeks\n\n**Customer Acquisition:**\n1. **Customer #1:** Former colleague (LinkedIn message)\n2. **Customer #2:** Indie Hackers post → DM conversation\n3. **Customer #3:** Cold outreach to 50 recruiters (2 replied, 1 bought)\n4. **Customer #4:** Partnership with recruiting podcast (guest appearance)\n5. **Customer #5:** Twitter thread about building in public (went semi-viral)\n\n**Total Revenue:** $2,500 MRR ($500/customer)\n\n**Key Lesson:** "The podcast guest spot was the highest ROI activity - \none appearance led to 3 customers!"\n\n---\n\n### Example 2: B2C App (First 10 Customers)\n\n**Product:** Fitness tracking app for busy parents\n\n**Timeline:** 6 weeks\n\n**Customer Acquisition:**\n1. **Customers #1-3:** Facebook parenting groups (helpful posts + soft pitch)\n2. **Customers #4-6:** Reddit r/fitness (AMA about fitness for parents)\n3. **Customers #7-8:** Instagram micro-influencer (barter: free premium for post)\n4. **Customers #9-10:** Product Hunt launch (#3 Product of the Day)\n\n**Total Revenue:** $490 MRR ($49/customer)\n\n**Key Lesson:** "Being genuinely helpful in communities worked way better \nthan direct advertising!"\n\n---\n\n### Example 3: Consulting Service (First 5 Clients)\n\n**Service:** SEO consulting for SaaS startups\n\n**Timeline:** 2 weeks\n\n**Client